I am used to hitting the &#x27;/&#x27; key to search in a web page. When I do it in bitbucket, it shows an "help" window describing the site-specific shortcuts. There are two issues with this:

# According to this same help window, the &#x27;/&#x27; key should focus the site search field, not bring up the help (maybe the fact that I have an AZERTY keyboard and need to press shift in order to make a &#x27;/&#x27; has something to do with this);
# There should be a way to configure the bitbucket shortcuts, or at least disable them so that they won&#x27;t conflict with my usual browser shortcuts. Of course, I can disable the shortcuts by disabling javascript on bitbucket, but this also disables some useful features (like the preview below the text area I&#x27;m typing into right now).

It would be very useful to have equations typeset by MathJax in the site Wiki. Here is an example of someone hacking Creole to do this:

https://github.com/scottt/jscreole

Thanks,

{code}
 Matt
{code}

