When deleting a remote git branch over ssh with command :\\
{{{\\
git push origin :branch_name\\
}}}

I see error message :\\
{{{\\
remote: fatal: bad object 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000\\
}}}

But everything seems ok on the repository and the web interface and the branch is correctly deleted.

h1. Andrew creates a repository, {{{andrew/foo}}}
h1. Bob starts following {{{andrew/foo}}}
h1. Courtney starts following {{{andrew/foo}}}
Andrew likely wants to see all three events in his newsfeed – who doesn&#x27;t enjoy an ego boost from time to time?

Bob, on the other hand, is probably not interested in the fact that Courtney now also follows this repository. Ideally, he&#x27;d see only the first two events in his newsfeed.

The issue tracker service creates multiple log entries in an issue report when a branch is merged into another branch and then that branch is pushed.

Example:\\
Create issue which gives an id of BCLOUD-5.

{code}
#!bash

git commit -a -m &#x27;My log. Fixes BCLOUD-5&#x27;
git push origin master
git checkout production
git merge master
git push origin production
{code}
